a-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eyt1665702720146.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eyt1665702720146.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eyt1665702720146.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eyt1665702720146\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Commit Processing\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__commit_processing_135293\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface maintains an internal list of the DBMSs that are currently open. When\n      executing a commit instruction, Uniface goes to each DBMS one by one, issuing a commit\n      instruction.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__topic_d28182e1_d28183e1_d28184e1_d28185e1_d28186e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d510253e53\">\n                        \n Without Two-Phase Commit\n </h2>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__fig_d43802e1_d43803e1_d43804e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Commit Processing Without Two-Phase Commit</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Commit processing without two-phase commit\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/commit_without_twophase.jpg?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 1. Commit Processing Without Two-Phase Commit\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/commit_without_twophase.jpg?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21806e1_d21807e1_d21808e1\">Send <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path1</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21809e1_d21810e1_d21811e1\">Send <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path2</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21812e1_d21813e1_d21814e1\">Send <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path3</code>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__topic_d28187e1_d28188e1_d28189e1_d28190e1_d28191e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d510253e99\">\n                        \n With Two-Phase Commit\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__p_d43811e1_d43812e1_d43813e1\">Uniface first issues a prepare to commit signal to all the DBMSs which support two-phase commit. If this operation succeeds, Uniface sends a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> to the DBMSs which do not support two-phase commit. The DBMSs from the first round then receive the final <code class=\"ph codeph\">commit</code> signal. This process is shown in the example in the figure:</p>\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__p_d43814e1_d43815e1_d43816e1\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__fig_w4318ab1b5b5b5b1_w4319ab1b5b5b5_w4320ab1b5b5_w4321ab1b5_w4322ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Commit Processing with Two-Phase Commit </figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Commit processing with two-phase commit\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/commit_with_twophase.jpg?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"Figure 2. Commit Processing with Two-Phase Commit \" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/commit_with_twophase.jpg?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21815e1_d21816e1_d21817e1\">Send <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> phase 1 to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path1</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21818e1_d21819e1_d21820e1\">Send <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> phase 1 to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path3</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21821e1_d21822e1_d21823e1\">Send <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path2</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21824e1_d21825e1_d21826e1\">Send commit phase 2 to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path1</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__li_d21827e1_d21828e1_d21829e1\">Send commit phase 2 to <code class=\"ph codeph\">$path3</code>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__topic_d28192e1_d28193e1_d28194e1_d28195e1_d28196e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d510253e171\">\n                        \n Rollback on Error\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__p_d43820e1_d43821e1_d43822e1\">If an error occurs at any point in the process, Uniface will only issue a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> if it is coded to do so in ProcScript, and only to the DBMSs which have not yet been committed. The possible areas of risk are when one DBMS has received the final <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span>, and the network fails before the next one can receive its final <code class=\"ph codeph\">commit</code> signal. If the network fails at either of these points, an incomplete transaction is committed.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__topic_d28197e1_d28198e1_d28199e1_d28200e1_d28201e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d510253e189\">\n                        \n Minimized Risks With Two-Phase Commits\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eyt1665702720146__p_d43826e1_d43827e1_d43828e1\">Every step is taken, however, to make this window of vulnerability small. Uniface first checks the logical integrity of a transaction before doing any modifications. It then checks whether all network connections are functioning before starting to commit. The highest risk is limited to the time between successive connector requests. This is generally a slight fraction of a second.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/etu1665703249143.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$TWO_PHASE_COMMIT</a><p>Enable two-phase commit functionality.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527396\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527396\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Commit Processing Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Commit Processing Uniface maintains an internal list of the DBMSs that are currently open. When executing a commit instruction, Uniface goes to each DBMS one by one, issuing a commit instruction. Without Two-Phase Commit Figure 1. Commit Processing Without Two-Phase Commit Send commit to $path1 Send commit to $path2 Send commit to $path3 With Two-Phase Commit Uniface first issues a prepare to commit signal to all the DBMSs which support two-phase commit. If this operation succeeds, Uniface sends a commit to the DBMSs which do not support two-phase commit. The DBMSs from the first round then receive the final commit signal. This process is shown in the example in the figure: Figure 2. Commit Processing with Two-Phase Commit Send commit phase 1 to $path1 Send commit phase 1 to $path3 Send commit to $path2 Send commit phase 2 to $path1 Send commit phase 2 to $path3 Rollback on Error If an error occurs at any point in the process, Uniface will only issue a rollback if it is coded to do so in ProcScript, and only to the DBMSs which have not yet been committed. The possible areas of risk are when one DBMS has received the final commit , and the network fails before the next one can receive its final commit signal. If the network fails at either of these points, an incomplete transaction is committed. Minimized Risks With Two-Phase Commits Every step is taken, however, to make this window of vulnerability small. Uniface first checks the logical integrity of a transaction before doing any modifications. It then checks whether all network connections are functioning before starting to commit. The highest risk is limited to the time between successive connector requests. This is generally a slight fraction of a second. Related Links $TWO_PHASE_COMMIT Enable two-phase commit functionality. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}